@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - dashboardservice/DashboardGroup
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired DashboardGroup spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetDashboardGroup;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListDashboardGroups using filters\ncompartmentId, displayName;
:Create the OCI resource via\nCreateDashboardGroup when no reusable match is\nfound;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteDashboardGroup with\nrequired via GetDashboardGroup or\nListDashboardGroups to DELETED, NOT_FOUND\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetDashboardGroup or\nListDashboardGroups until OCI reaches DELETED,\nNOT_FOUND;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId, systemTags;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeDashboardGroupCompartment,\nUpdateDashboardGroup only for mutable fields\ndefinedTags, description, displayName,\nfreeformTags;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=read-after-write;\nupdate=read-after-write; delete=confirm-delete;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: dashboardservice
slug: dashboardgroup
kind: DashboardGroup
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=read-after-write;
update=read-after-write; delete=confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, description,
displayName, freeformTags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, systemTags
create-only fields: none
list lookup:
oci_dashboard_service_dashboard_groups filters
compartmentId, displayName; exact compartmentId
plus displayName unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING; empty displayName skips
lookup and duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal and DELETED is the delete-confirmation
target.
Existing-before-create lookup runs only when
both compartmentId and displayName are present,
then scopes ListDashboardGroups by exact
compartmentId plus displayName and reuses only a
unique candidate in ACTIVE, CREATING, or
UPDATING.
Only displayName, description, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place. The handwritten
update builder preserves clear-to-empty intent
for those fields, while compartmentId and
systemTags remain replacement-only drift and
ChangeDashboardGroupCompartment stays out of
scope.
Create, get, and update return the
DashboardGroup body directly, delete returns
headers only, and the Dashboards home-region
caveat remains explicit in the published runtime
contract.
end note
@enduml
